MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "#### What is the problem?\r\nFollow up to https://github.com/datalad/datalad/pull/2922#issuecomment-429996043\r\n\r\nIf `run` fails, repo could be left in a dirty state with some new  and/or changed (unlocked) files.  User would need to figure out not only how to fix his command to run, but also how to revert back to the clean state.  So it would be nice to give either specific instruction or hints (\"Use `git reset --hard && git clean -dfx` to get to the clean state before running the command again\")\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2924/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2924/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}